Samsung has announced that the 512GB version of its Galaxy Note 9 smartphone is now available in South Africa. The device also boasts 8GB of RAM and support for a 512GB microSD slot, meaning users can access 1TB of total storage on the device if they wish. “The 512GB Note 9 is a powerhouse that takes storage to unprecedented levels,” said Samsung South Africa Integrated Mobility director Justin Hume. “The release of this model will undoubtedly be welcomed by those who want a smartphone that goes well beyond the norm.” Samsung’s 512GB version of its Galaxy Note 9 has been in high demand worldwide, which resulted in shipping delays for the product. Samsung said the Galaxy Note 9 512GB is now available in Ocean Blue for R25,999.